\frametitle{Appendix B --- Full Ablation Table}
\protect\phantomsection\label{appendix-b-full-ablation-table}
This appendix complements the rule-family ablation reported in Section 9
of the main text (which uses \texttt{flask\_app} and \texttt{calculator}
as ablation targets) by reconstructing the same analysis on
\texttt{zoo/01\_simple\_state} --- the smallest non-trivial fixture in
the evaluation set and the one used to demonstrate the runnable
active-inference cycle in Section 5. Because zoo/01 has a single
hidden-state factor, a single observation modality, two actions, and no
POLICY/CONTEXT/CONSTRAINT nodes in the origin, the ablations isolate
each rule family's contribution to the minimal POMDP skeleton.

The ablation protocol is identical to Section 9: reconstruct the deltas
from the rule-to-\texttt{MappingKind} assignment recorded in
\texttt{../cogant/docs/evaluation/ACTIVE\_INFERENCE\_MAPPING.md} and the
mapping-kind breakdown for zoo/01 extracted from the empirical run in
\texttt{../cogant/docs/evaluation/EMPIRICAL\_CLAIM.md}. The deltas below
reflect the conflict-resolution semantics of the engine: when two
families both emit the same \texttt{MappingKind}, removing one family
shifts the mapping to the secondary producer rather than removing it
outright.

\begin{block}{B.1 Rule-family ablation on zoo/01\_simple\_state}
\protect\phantomsection\label{b.1-rule-family-ablation-on-zoo01_simple_state}
\textbf{Baseline (all 5 families enabled).}
\texttt{semantic\_mappings.json} for zoo/01 contains 4 mappings: 1
HIDDEN\_STATE (\texttt{BeliefState} class, mutating \texttt{self.state}
attribute), 1 OBSERVATION (\texttt{get\_state}, read-only getter), 2
ACTION (\texttt{update\_state} with two overloaded semantics). The GNN
bundle declares \texttt{s\_f0{[}3{]}}, \texttt{o\_m0{[}1{]}},
\texttt{u\_c0}, \texttt{u\_c1}; semantic coverage 80.0 \%, validator
100.0 / 100, ε = 1.0000 roundtrip.

\textbf{Table B.1 --- Rule-family ablation on
\texttt{zoo/01\_simple\_state} (baseline: 4 mappings, ε = 1.0000, GNN
validator = 100.0).}

