\begin{longtable}[]{@{}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\linewidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.1626}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\linewidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.3008}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\linewidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.5366}}@{}}
\toprule\noalign{}
\begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
Appendix B family
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
Section 9 family
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
Primary Section 9 rule(s)
\end{minipage} \\
\midrule\noalign{}
\endhead
StateSpaceRule & Structural & \texttt{MutatingSubsystemRule},
\texttt{ReadOnlyInputRule} \\
ObservationRule & Semantic & \texttt{ObservationRule},
\texttt{PolicyRule}, \texttt{ContextRule} \\
ActionRule & Semantic & \texttt{ActionRule},
\texttt{OrchestratorRule} \\
ConstraintRule & Semantic + Behavioural & \texttt{PreferenceRule},
\texttt{TestAssertionRule} \\
FallbackRule & Matrix-fallback (Section 9 Table 12) &
\texttt{compute\_A}, \texttt{compute\_B}, \texttt{compute\_C},
\texttt{compute\_D} fallback paths \\
\bottomrule\noalign{}
\end{longtable}
}

The Section 9 ablation is fixture-level (\texttt{flask\_app},
\texttt{calculator}) and reports mapping-count deltas; the Appendix B
ablation is role-level (HS, OBS, ACT, CNST, fallback) and reports ε
deltas on the minimum-complexity fixture that still round-trips
perfectly. The two ablations are complementary: together they bracket
the failure surface from ``largest real-world fixture'' down to
``smallest runnable POMDP''.
\end{block}
